The project focusses on community engagement approach through the organization of women into development teams and one-to-five networks, aims to evaluate its impact on health improvement with the objective of developing appropriate community engagement approach for adoption into the health strategic plan.</gtr:impact><gtr:partnerContribution>The Borena Zonal Health Department provided office facility to the research team at the field site. It also provided additional vehicle to support the field work during the survey period. The Borena Zonal Health Department also relieved some of its health workers from their primary responsibility of working at health centers, hospitals, and district and zonal offices to work temporarly with our research team during survey. This is in addition to the secondement of one staff described in the respective section. 

